long_desc.thetext:
Snippet:

   List<String> test(String[] args) {
      return Arrays.asList(args);
   }

Selecting "asList" gives an IMethod that represents the invocation "List<String> asList(String[])", good.

Passing this IMethod into ASTParser.createBinding() returns an IMethodBinding for "List<T> asList(T[])", which looks wrong to me.

This was detected as the root cause behind the difference discussed in bug 403917 comment 10 last para.

Please let me know if it may have been a deliberate decision to ignore the parameterization.
